http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Thiruvananthapuram/Case-registered-against-Shiv-Sena-activists/article14003166.ece

The Museum police have registered a case against nearly 200 identifiable persons who were involved in the demonstration organised in protest against the concert of Pakistani ghazal maestro Ghulam Ali on Friday.The activists of the Shiv Sena were blocked by the police a short distance away from the Nishagandhi Auditorium, the venue of the concert.ProtestWater cannons had to be used to disperse the agitators, who also burnt a Pakistan flag as a mark of protest.According to the police, the activists have been booked under Section 143, 147 and 149 (for unlawful assembly) and Section 283 (obstructing traffic) of the Indian Penal Code.